column5: Lots of damaged boats here for our friends down south. Clearly snow was not a consideration when the facilities were constructed...and why would it be?  http://di-vo.net/diozarks/
Wow! Unbelieveable pictures!!!  Thanks for posting...just goes to show you the messed up weather we've been experiencing lately!
This makes me love my barebones aluminium.simple storage no bells and whistles to break.Imagine how many millions damage in this area.Its going to hurt!Mike

Well, snow has a lot of weight to it, and it doesn't drain off of a roof. There's certainly been some weird weather happenings in the past decade or so. And more to come I'm sure. Lake Superior is down 20" right now. And that's a lot of water. Water that is somewhere else on the planet causing major flooding. Strange stuff indeed. Strange, but scary.
I was in Eagle Rock,Missouri on business 4 days before that storm hit.The temp. was 75 F. the day that I headed home.Seems somewhat odd  seeng those pictures now.
Pretty wild stuff, covers definetly weren't designed for snow load. Don't know if I'd want to be the one shoveling snow off the covers though.
